## 4. Enterprise Compliance Guidelines

Organizations deploying this software at scale must follow industry-standard OSS governance and corporate compliance requirements:

### Mandatory Controls

* Include the LICENSE and NOTICE files in all internal or external distributions
* Conduct internal code review and security audit before production deployment
* Maintain comprehensive change logs for all modified components
* Ensure all third-party dependencies meet compliance requirements
* Implement proper version control and source code management
* Document all customizations and configuration changes

### Legal & Compliance Requirements

* Review and approve open-source licenses with legal counsel
* Maintain Software Bill of Materials (SBOM)
* Track license obligations and restrictions
* Implement IP compliance policies
* Conduct regular compliance audits
* Ensure GDPR, HIPAA, SOC2, or other regulatory compliance as applicable

### Recommended Disclosures

Include the following in your compliance bundle or product documentation:

**Standard Attribution:**
```
This product includes open-source components from the IAC Dharma Platform.
Copyright © 2024-2025 Raghavendra Deshpande
Licensed under the MIT License
```

